translated:
Öberg, Lars Harald, district physician, Skene, b. 15/7/90 in Agnetorp, Ska-rab. 1., son of landowner Carl Ö. and Frida Andersson. Married in 1921 to Stina Svensson. Children: Lars (b. 1922), Anders (b. 1926), Brita (b. 1931). 

Education: Passed student exam in Karlstad in 1909, medical candidate in 1915, medical licentiate in 1921 at the Karolinska Institute. Employed as a physician at Vadstena Hospital from 1918-1919, as a junior physician at Målilla Sanatorium from 1921-1922, temporary junior physician at Karls-hamn Hospital in 1922 and 1923, assistant physician in the surgical department at Sahlgr. Hospital from 1922-1923, district physician and hospital physician in Högsäter district from 1923-1932, temporary junior physician in Vänersib in 1928, district physician in Skene district since 1932. Chairman of Köpmannebro Municipality from 1929-1932, chairman of Örby Parish Health Committee from 1932-1938.
